macro_markets.query: What are the most important macroeconomic and stock market news and developments from the past 24 hours? Include major index movements, Fed/central bank news, and significant company earnings or announcements.

items.title: US Stock Market Mixed as Dow Falls 0.6%, S&P 500 Edges Up
items.summary: The Dow Jones Industrial Average declined 285.30 points (-0.6%) to 49,098.71, while the S&P 500 rose 0.1% and Nasdaq gained 0.3%. The Russell 2000 fell 1.8%, weighed down by weakness in financials and utilities.

items.title: Intel Shares Plunge 17% on Disappointing AI Chip Guidance
items.summary: Intel's stock price fell as much as 17% on Friday following disappointing earnings guidance and challenges in meeting AI chip demand, marking a significant setback for the semiconductor sector.

items.title: Tesla Surges 4% on Elon Musk's FSD and Robotaxi Announcements
items.summary: Tesla's share price rose 4% on Thursday after CEO Elon Musk announced at Davos that full self-driving approval is expected in Europe and China by February, with widespread robotaxi deployment across the US by year-end.

items.title: USD/JPY Falls Below 155 Amid Joint US-Japan Intervention Concerns
items.summary: The USD/JPY currency pair dropped below 155 after tumbling over 1.7% on Friday, as markets anticipate potential coordinated intervention between Japan and the US to address speculative FX moves.

items.title: Fed Expected to Hold Rates at 3.75% This Week
items.summary: The Federal Reserve is anticipated to maintain interest rates at 3.75% during its Wednesday meeting, with markets also monitoring policy guidance and President Trump's nomination of a new Fed Chair.

items.title: Stock Market Signals Warn of Potential 2026 Inflation Rebound
items.summary: Market indicators show a rotation from growth to value stocks and increased interest in small-caps, historically preceding inflationary pressures. JPMorgan projects no Fed rate cuts in 2026 and a potential rate hike in 2027.

items.title: Four Magnificent Seven Companies Report Earnings This Week
items.summary: Microsoft, Meta, Tesla, and Apple are scheduled to report earnings this week, with investor focus on whether companies are reaping benefits from AI-related investments amid elevated market valuations.

items.title: US Dollar Index Signals Long-Term Bearish Trend
items.summary: The US Dollar Index printed its largest bearish candlestick since April 2025 last week, closing at its lowest weekly level since June 2025, indicating sustained downward pressure on the currency.

crypto_news.query: What are the most significant cryptocurrency and blockchain news from the past 24 hours? Include major price movements, regulatory news, and notable project developments.

items.title: Bitcoin Falls Below $87,000, Erasing January Gains Amid Geopolitical and Economic Pressures
items.summary: Bitcoin dropped below $87,000 on January 26, marking a -0.5% return for the month after peaking at $97,000 earlier, driven by geopolitical risks, reduced safe-haven appeal, slower Fed rate cuts, ETF outflows, and market deleveraging.

items.title: Crypto Market Dips as Bitcoin Languishes 30% Below Peak, Gold Surges to $5,098
items.summary: Bitcoin fell 1.87% to $87,155 in 24 hours, Ethereum dropped 3.4% to $2,843, and Solana declined 3.95% to $121.35, with total market cap at $2.95 trillion down 1.74%; Fear and Greed Index hit 'extreme fear' at 20.

items.title: Upcoming US Regulatory Events for Crypto: SEC-CFTC Meeting and Senate Bill Markup
items.summary: The SEC and CFTC hold a joint crypto event on Tuesday, while the Senate Agriculture Committee marks up cryptocurrency market structure legislation on Monday; Senator Gillibrand is optimistic despite Democratic disagreements.

ai_news.query: What are the most important artificial intelligence and machine learning news and developments from the past 24 hours? Include new model releases, company announcements, research breakthroughs, and industry trends.

items.title: KAIST Develops AI Framework to Predict Battery Cathode Particle Size with Reliability Metrics
items.summary: Researchers at KAIST have created a machine learning model using NGBoost and MatImpute to accurately predict battery material particle sizes from incomplete data, providing prediction uncertainty for reliable decision-making in battery development. The framework reduces unnecessary experiments and accelerates next-generation battery material design.

items.title: Grab Acquires Chinese AI Robotics Startup Infermove to Boost Delivery Automation
items.summary: Singapore-based Grab Holdings has acquired Infermove, enhancing its AI robotics for first- and last-mile logistics using imitation and reinforcement learning from real-world rider data. The 'Rider Shadow System' addresses data acquisition challenges in embodied AI for complex delivery environments.

items.title: Former Google GM Launches Fermi.ai, an AI-First Edtech Platform for STEM Education
items.summary: Peeyush Ranjan, ex-Google General Manager, introduced Fermi.ai targeting personalized STEM learning in the US and India, with plans to expand subjects and a 2026 pilot for educators and schools.

items.title: Microsoft Azure Announces Storage Innovations and AI Governance Updates for 2026
items.summary: Azure is evolving storage into a unified intelligent platform supporting massive AI datasets, with Blob scaled accounts, NVIDIA DGX integrations, and new third-party tools like LangChain for enterprise AI training and inference.

items.title: FiberMall Unveils Next-Generation Optical Networking to Support Surging AI Data Center Demand
items.summary: FiberMall launched solutions to minimize latency and boost throughput in AI infrastructure, addressing bandwidth bottlenecks from LLMs and generative AI in data centers.

gaming.query: What are the most notable video game and gaming industry news from the past 24 hours? Include game releases, announcements, esports, and industry developments.

items.title: Cult of the Lamb: Woolhaven and Arknights: Endfield Release on January 25
items.summary: Two highly anticipated games, Cult of the Lamb: Woolhaven and Arknights: Endfield, officially released on Thursday, impacting fantasy gaming league scores and pushing one team into second place.

items.title: Bandai Namco Announces Dragon Ball Project AGE 1000 for 2027
items.summary: Bandai Namco revealed Dragon Ball project AGE 1000, featuring new world and characters by Akira Toriyama, set for release in 2027 with more details at Dragon Ball Games Battle Hour 2026.

items.title: Forza Horizon 6 Release Date Confirmed for May 19, 2026
items.summary: Forza Horizon 6 received an official release date of Tuesday, May 19, 2026, and is now available for pre-order on Steam and Xbox.

items.title: Dragon Ball: Sparking! ZERO Announces Major DLC and Free Updates
items.summary: New major DLC announced for Dragon Ball: Sparking! ZERO alongside free updates including Mission 100 mode on January 26 and Survival Mode in Spring.

items.title: Marathon and Fable Receive Release Date and Season Updates
items.summary: Marathon got a firm release date, while Fable was assigned a season in ongoing gaming updates alongside other title announcements.

tech_news.query: What are the most important technology news and developments from the past 24 hours? Include major product launches, company news, and significant tech industry developments. Exclude AI-specific news.

items.title: Intel Shares Plunge 17% on Disappointing Guidance
items.summary: Intel's stock dropped as much as 17% after issuing weak guidance and facing challenges in meeting chip demand. This contributed to sector volatility ahead of major tech earnings.

items.title: Netskope Releases 2026 Cloud and Threat Report
items.summary: Netskope launched its 2026 report highlighting key cybersecurity trends, including a threefold rise in SaaS genAI app usage and doubled incidents of sensitive data sent to AI apps.

items.title: CrowdStrike and Nord Security Partner for SMB Cybersecurity
items.summary: CrowdStrike and Nord Security announced a partnership integrating Falcon platform with secure access solutions to bolster defenses for small-to-medium businesses facing rising threats.

items.title: Fujitsu Launches Autonomous AI Management Platform
items.summary: Fujitsu introduced a new platform built around its Takane large language model for enterprises to autonomously manage generative AI, featuring high-precision Japanese performance and reduced memory use.

items.title: CompTIA Reports Flat Tech Hiring in December
items.summary: U.S. tech employment remained neutral in December with a net loss of 1,461 positions across technical and non-technical roles, according to CompTIA analysis.

items.title: Deel Faces DOJ Criminal Probe Over Alleged Corporate Espionage
items.summary: Deel is under DOJ investigation for reportedly recruiting a spy at rival Rippling, with grand-jury subpoenas issued to gather information.

items.title: Nvidia's Vera Rubin GPU Enters Full Production
items.summary: Nvidia announced Vera Rubin GPU is in full production for 2026 ramp-up, promising 5X performance, 10X throughput, and 10X better token cost over Blackwell.
